## Addition & Multiplication Laws

### Addition Law

Applies for 2 or more mutually exclusive events. When 2 events are mutually exclusive, it means that they cannot happen at the same time

### 2. Multiplication Law

Applies for 2 or more independent events. When 2 events are independent, it means that the occurrence of one of them has no influence on the occurrence of the other

